WEBSITE FROM SCRATCH PROJECT

Overview:
Choose a real or fictional business and create a website completely from scratch.
The project is divided into THREE parts:
1. Content
2. Design
3. Interactivity

You will plan and justify your choices before implementation.

--------------------------------------------------
PART 1: CONTENT (Answer ALL questions, add your own if necessary)

1. What is the name of your business?
The business name is Choopan Grill.


2. Is the business real or fictional?
Choopan Grill  is a real Business.


3. What products or services does the business offer?
Choopan Grill offers a variety of traditional Afghan dishes. 
The menu includes appetizers, soups, salads, and grilled kebabs such as chicken kebab, lamb tikka, and kofta.
The restaurant provides freshly prepared meals for customers who want authentic Afghan cuisine.

4. Who is the target audience?
The target audience includes:
People who enjoy international food
Families looking for traditional meals
Students and local residents
Anyone interested in trying Afghan cuisine

5. What problem does this business solve?
The restaurant provides a place where customers can enjoy authentic Afghan food that may not be available in many other restaurants.


6. What makes this business unique compared to competitors?
Choopan Grill stands out because it focuses on traditional Afghan recipes and freshly grilled kebabs. The dishes are made with authentic ingredients and represent Afghan culture and cooking traditions.


7. What pages will your website include (e.g., Home, About, Services, Contact)?
The website will include the following pages:
•	Home page
•	About page
•	Menu page
•	Contact page



8. Write a short mission statement for the business.
The mission of Choopan Grill is to share the taste of Afghan cuisine by serving fresh food and providing a welcoming place for customers to enjoy traditional meals.


9. What tone should the website content have (professional, friendly, modern, etc.)?
The tone of the website will be friendly, welcoming, and easy to understand.


10. What call-to-action do you want visitors to take?
Visitors should be encouraged to visit the restaurant and try the menu items.


11. What information must be immediately visible on the homepage?
The homepage should clearly show:
•	The restaurant name
•	A picture of the food or restaurant
•	A short welcome message
•	A navigation menu to access other pages
•	A link to the menu


12. Will the site include images, videos, or other media? Why?
Yes, the website will include images of food and the restaurant. Images make the website more appealing and help visitors see what dishes are offered.



--------------------------------------------------
PART 2: DESIGN (Answer ALL questions, add your own if necessary)

1. What overall style will the website have (minimalist, corporate, creative, etc.)?
The website will have a simple and clean restaurant style that focuses on the food and menu.


2. What color scheme will you use and why?
The color scheme will include dark red, black, and white. These colors are commonly used in restaurant websites and create a warm and comfortable feeling.

3. What fonts will you use for headings and body text?
A bold font will be used for headings to make them stand out, and a simple readable font will be used for the body text.

4. How will spacing and layout improve readability?
Spacing between sections, images, and text will make the content easier to read and prevent the page from looking crowded.


6. What visual hierarchy will guide the user’s attention?
Larger headings, images, and menu sections will help guide the user’s attention to the most important information on the page.


7. How will consistency be maintained across pages?
All pages will use the same navigation bar, colors, fonts, and layout style so the website looks consistent.

8. What icons will you use?
Simple icons may be used for location, contact information, and menu items.

9. What emotions should the design evoke in users?
The design should make visitors feel comfortable, interested in the food, and excited to try the dishes.

10. How will accessibility be considered (contrast, font size, etc.)?
Accessibility will be considered by:
•	Using readable font sizes
•	Ensuring good color contrast
•	Keeping the navigation simple and clear



11. What inspiration sources influenced your design?
The design is inspired by modern restaurant websites that focus on food images and simple navigation.

12. Describe the layout of the homepage and build the wireframe
The homepage will include the following sections:
1.	Navigation bar with links to other pages
2.	A large image of the restaurant or food
3.	A welcome message introducing Choopan Grill
4.	A preview of menu items
5.	Contact information at the bottom
Simple wireframe example:
--------------------------------
LOGO | HOME | ABOUT | MENU | CONTACT
--------------------------------

        LARGE FOOD IMAGE

      Welcome to Choopan Grill
      Traditional Afghan Food

--------------------------------
          MENU PREVIEW
--------------------------------

          CONTACT INFO
--------------------------------
 

--------------------------------------------------
PART 3: INTERACTIVITY (Answer ALL questions, add your own if necessary)

1. What interactive elements will your site include (forms, buttons, menus, etc.)?
The website will include navigation menus, buttons, and a contact form.


2. How will users navigate the website?
Users will navigate using the navigation bar at the top of the page, which links to the Home, About, Menu, and Contact pages.

3. Will there be form validation or user feedback? Explain.
Yes. The contact form will require users to fill in important fields such as name and message before submitting.


4. What JavaScript functionality will you implement?
JavaScript may be used to add simple interactions such as form validation or button effects

5. How does interactivity improve user experience?
Interactivity allows users to easily move between pages, interact with forms, and explore the menu, which makes the website easier and more enjoyable to use. 


--------------------------------------------------
RUBRIC (100 POINTS TOTAL)

Content (40 points)
- Business concept clarity (10 pts)
- Completeness of answers (10 pts)
- Quality and relevance of written content (10 pts)
- Organization and structure (10 pts)

Design (40 points)
- Visual consistency and aesthetics (10 pts)
- Effective color and font choices (10 pts)
- Layout and usability (10 pts)
- Accessibility and responsiveness considerations (10 pts)

Interactivity (20 points)
- Appropriate use of interactive elements (10 pts)
- Functionality and usability (10 pts)

--------------------------------------------------
Submission Requirements:

How to submit:
* Everything is to be posted on GitHub and the website need to be hosted on [GitHub Pages](https://docs.github.com/en/pages/getting-started-with-github-pages/creating-a-github-pages-site)
* Submit only the GitHub Repo and Website URL link on Brightspace

What to include in the repo:
- Web Design Document: this will be the README.md file in your repo. This includes :
	= all the questions as well as your answers
	= any external resources used (links)
	= wireframe design (hand-drawn/computer-aided)
	= main sections to include:
		+ project overview
		+ target audience
		+ content strategy
		+ information organization
		+ visual desing (wireframe and more)
		+ interaction / functionality
		+ technical overview
		+ timeline / project milestone
- The website files (HTML, CSS, JS)
	= Code must be original and well-commented

--------------------------------------------------
Extra Credit Opportunity
- Design the website to be accessible
- Design the website for a real business
- Design the website to be responsive (mobile vs desktop)
 












